  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package carries a post-signing evidence update: one validation result was appended after the package was signed without re-signing, introducing a future-dated evidence inconsistency (W-CON-03). The narrative notes the package was 'updated post-signing' to incorporate late-arriving experimental data from an independent hemolysis measurement campaign.",
